In this room, there is a large desk. On it are the remains of crystal balls and other magical artifacts; all now broken. As you entered the room, a panel on the door slammed shut. Then it glowed a pale blue. No one can pry it open.  Next, the door on the other side of the room glow bright orange, inviting the party to use it

As the party enters the room, the door slams shut, glows orange and vanishes! A door appears to the right. A voice, coming from the ceiling addresses you: "Congratulations, brave adventurers! Today you have proved yourself to me and are now ready to start your quest! Years ago, my amulet was stolen by the evil wizard Werdnat.  Werdna hides in the maze somewhere below us. Find him; slay him; and return to me the amulet! (...)  To aid you in your quest, I will give you a blue ribbon, which may be used to enter the elevator on this floor. Go now -- And may the gods guide you!"
A sign on the door reads: "Treasure repository."

In this room is a statue of a monster with the body of a chicken and the head of a cat. The statue is made of bronze, and lies on an onyx pedestal.  There are unusual runes on a plaque thereon. Gold key
As you enter this room, a bronze smoke fills it. You feel compelled to leave immdediately! Need bronze key
As you enter this room, a silvery fog evelops you. Terrible demons form all around you. In terror, you flee from the room! Need silver key

The dust on the floor is disturbed here. There seems to be the tracks of a small animal leading off eastwards!
The stone walls here are covered in unusual quarry marks. They look very old.
The dust in front of you has been disturbed recently by something other than a small animal!
You feel a faint breeze coming from down the corridor to the East!
You are enveloped in an unnatural darkness here!
The door here has at some time in the past been knocked off its hinges...
A few rotten scraps of cloth lie here. Scribbed on the wall above them is some graffiti. Most of it is unintellignle but you can make out the words "Kadorto is a Lie!"
The remains of a large wooden sign hang from the wall. At one time it said "Area out of bounds!!!" but it has been heavily defaced over the long passage of time.

A strange glow seems to emanate from this room. In the center, a smallish man in a long robe turns towards the party and shouts "Begone, strangers!" He slowly waves his hands, and chants "mapiro mahama diromat!!" teleported back to castle

In this room is a silver statue of a boar with horns and long fangs. On the wall by the statue is a message (partially obscured) that appeard to have been left by passing elves. It is hardly legible. But some comments warning bout ghosts and demons can still be made out Silver key
There is a gem encrusted statue of a hooded man here. A golden light emanates from the hood. In front of the statue is an altar, in which pungent incense is burning Murphy's Ghost
